      "grammar": {
        "title": "Weather verbs",
        "body": "Weather uses the dummy subject **il**, like English \"it\": **il pluve** (it rains), **il nive** (it snows), **il face frigide** (it's cold ‚ÄĒ literally 'it makes cold').\nCommon weather adjectives: **calide** (hot), **frigide** (cold), **nubilose** (cloudy)."
